1. The "Transaction-Safe" Backend (The "Senior" Move)
Right now, you are probably doing two separate inserts for an order. If the second one fails, your database is corrupted.
God-Level Move: Use a PostgreSQL Stored Procedure (RPC) in Supabase.
Why? This ensures "Atomicity." Either the whole order (Order + Items + Inventory check) happens, or nothing happens. No "ghost orders."
Resume Line: "Implemented atomic database transactions via Postgres RPC to prevent data inconsistency during high-traffic peak hours."
2. The Staff "Kanban" Dashboard (The Product Heart)
Recruiters love seeing the "Admin Side." Build a dashboard for the canteen staff that looks like Trello.
God-Level Move: Three columns: Pending | Preparing | Ready.
Feature: Staff should be able to "Drag and Drop" an order from one column to the next.
Feature: Add a "Sound Notification." When a new order arrives, the kitchen hears a "Ding!" This makes it feel like a real product.
3. Real-Time "Live Track" (The UX Wow Factor)
Don't make the student refresh the page.
God-Level Move: Use Supabase Realtime.
The Experience: When the staff clicks "Ready," the student's success screen instantly turns Green, starts an animation, and shows: "Token #45 is hot and ready! Collect now."
Resume Line: "Leveraged WebSockets (Supabase Realtime) to eliminate manual polling, reducing server load and improving UX latency by 90%."
4. QR Code Verification (The Security Piece)
How does the staff know the student isn't lying about their token?
God-Level Move: Use a library like qrcode.react. When an order is placed, generate a unique QR code on the student's screen.
The Experience: The staff "scans" it (or clicks it) to mark it as COLLECTED. This prevents token fraud.
